quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  10,43,"And of them are some who look at you. But can you guide the blind, though they cannot see"
  10,44,"Verily, Allah wrongs not man in aught, but men do wrong themselves"
  10,45,"And on the day when We will gather them together, it will be as though they had not stayed save an hour of the day. They shall know each other. Lost will be those who denied the meeting with Allah, and were not guided"
  10,46,"Whether We show you something of that which We promised them, or whether We will take you to Ourself, still unto Us is their return; and Allah is also a witness to what they do"
  10,47,"To every people was sent a Messenger; and when their Messenger comes to them (on the Day of Judgment), it will be judged between them fairly, and they will not be wronged"
  10,48,"But they say, \"When will this promise come to pass, if you tell the truth"
  10,49,"Say, \"I have no power to harm or profit myself (or I have no power myself to harm or profit), save what Allah wills. Every nation has its appointed time; when their appointed time comes to them they cannot delay it for an hour or hasten it"
  10,50,"Say, \"Have you considered, when His punishment comes to you, by night or day, which portion thereof will the sinners wish to hasten"
  10,51,"And when it has fallen on you, will you believe in it. What! Believe now, when you wished to hasten it through unbelief"
  10,52,"Then shall it be said to those who have done wrong, \"Taste you the torment of Eternity! Are you recompensed except for that which you have earned"
  10,53,"They will ask you to inform them whether it be true. Say, \"Yea, by my Lord! Verily, it is the truth, nor can you escape"